post_text: The small things that could be sabotaging your weight loss goals.
comment_message: I started doing some of these tips 2 years ago. Added one tip and stayed with it. Then another and another. Started with light exercise to get into shape again. Then slowly progressed. Now I am down 50 lbs. Skinnier, stronger and more athletic than I was at 18. Everyday I am in the best shape of my life because I am better than I was yesterday. I think before I eat. I always have a plan for nutrition (thanks to my wonderful wife Yesenia Yocum) and exercise (thank you Beachbody.com). Fyi, I do not diet, I do not believe in fad diets because they are all recipes for failure as they are not sustainable (looking at you Keto diet). I chose healthy real foods that have simple real ingredients that I love. If you don't love it, you will hate it over time. That is why diets are proven to fail. I limit C.R.A.P intake. Carbonated sugar water (soda). Refined carbs - white sugar and flour (eat complex carbs like oats and whole wheat and non processed sugars like honey, Apple sauce and bananas). And Processed foods. If you do not know what half the ingredients are, put it back. It took me 13 years to gain the 50 lbs and only a year to lose it. I have kept it off for a year now following tips in the article. I truly hope this post can help someone out there start their own wellness journey. Cheers!

post_text: Thinking of replacing your carb habit with high-fat foods?
comment_message: I know people who have been doing Keto successfully for years. It has helped people with diabetes, high cholesterol, high BP and lose weight. Also has helped to minimize medication or get rid of them altogether. As a diabetic myself, I've been told by my doctor to do Low Carb to lose weight and to help control diabetes. Keto is very similar to Low Carb so to obtain good health with Keto is possible. There are more amazing success stories than bad experiences. Just as with any dietary changes you have to do things in moderation. A person can't gorge themselves on bacon every  day and expect no side effects. But just like any life style change you should always include a dietary health professional. I think if a person got sick from doing Keto they weren't doing it right.  Keto can be customized to each individual. They even now have Keto for vegans which I find very intriguing.

post_text: Thinking of replacing your carb habit with high-fat foods?
comment_message: Wrong! This type of high fat Keto diet is done for medical reasons ONLY. Like seizures in children. Keto done right for weight loss or body remodeling uses the fat you already stored on your body. If your tank is full you wouldn't put more gas in it would you now? Therefore 70% or thereabouts should be protein, 10 to 20 % carbs and the rest good fats.
